     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 84 +[38;2;248;248;242m| Setting | Default | Purpose |[99X[m[99C       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 85 +[38;2;248;248;242m|---------|---------|---------|[99X[m[99C       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 86 +[38;2;248;248;242m| **Beam width** | 50 | How many candidate rules are kept at each search depth. Higher = more exhaustive, slower. |[15X[m[15C       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 87 +[38;2;248;248;242m| **Max rule depth** | 3 | Longest rule allowed. `3` means rules of the form `A AND B AND C`. |[35X[m[35C       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 88 +[38;2;248;248;242m| **Min cases per rule** | 30 | Rules that would affect fewer than this many cases are discarded as too small to be actionable. | [m       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 89 +[38;2;248;248;242m| **Min lift** | 1.2 | The in-rule outcome rate must exceed the baseline by at least this factor (1.2 = at least 20% higher than b[m       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m    +[38;2;248;248;242maseline). |[119X[m[119C       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 90 +[38;2;248;248;242m| **FDR alpha** | 0.05 | Benjamini-Hochberg significance threshold for controlling false discoveries across the rule search. |    [m       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 91 +[38;2;248;248;242m| **Max drivers returned** | 20 | Upper bound on the number of rules shown in the full-table view. |[30X[m[30C       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 92 +[38;2;248;248;242m| **Redundancy Jaccard** | 0.9 | Rules whose case sets overlap by more than this fraction are treated as duplicates and filtered. [m       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m    +[38;2;248;248;242m|[129X[m[129C       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m 93 +[38;2;248;248;242m| **Sampling threshold** | 2,000,000 cases | Datasets above this size are deterministically sampled down using Floyd's combination[m       
     [38;2;80;200;80m[48;2;2;40;0m    + [38;2;248;248;242malgorithm. The output reports `WasSampled = true` and the actual sample size. |[50X[m[50C       
