  [1mWhat I added to the page (sourced from [38;2;177;185;249mmindzieWeb/Documentation/CalculatorCausalAnalysis_User_Guide.md [m[1mand the engine source at [22m                 [38;2;177;185;249m[1m[46;3Hmindzie.Engine.FilterAndCalculator/Calculator/AI/CausalAnalysis/[m[1m):[22m 

  1. [1mHow[22m [1mit[22m [1mcompares[22m [1mto[22m [1mRoot[22m [1mCause[22m [1mAnalysis[22m — capability table making the correlation-vs-causation contrast explicit.[K[30C
  2. [1mAdvanced[22m [1mSettings[22m [1mtable[22m — the real defaults: Beam width 50, Max depth 3, Min cases 30, Min lift 1.2, FDR alpha 0.05, Max returned 20,[K[9C
  Redundancy Jaccard 0.9, sampling threshold 2M.[99C
  3. [1mInterpreting[22m [1mthe[22m [1mResults[22m — the four evidence badges (Causal / Likely Causal / Associated / Correlational) with an example narrative.[K[10C
  4. [1mHow[22m [1mthe[22m [1mAlgorithm[22m [1mWorks[22m — six-stage pipeline:[K[97C
    - Preparation + MDL-optimal outcome-aware binning for numerics[81C
    - Bitmap indexing (bitwise AND for rule coverage)[94C
    - Beam-search subgroup discovery with depth-1/2/3 expansion and Jaccard redundancy filter[54C
    - Statistical significance: risk ratio, 95% Wilson CI, p-value, Benjamini-Hochberg FDR[57C
    - Causal adjudication: Bayesian structural signal + ridge-regularised logistic-regression propensity score[37C
    - Narrative generation[121C
  5. [1mPerformance[22m — timing table up to 1M cases; note on deterministic Floyd's-sampling above 2M.[K[51C
  6. [1mKnown[22m [1mLimitations[22m [1m(v1)[22m — binary outcomes only, no per-case explanations, no temporal drift split.[K[45C
